        "insights": "\u05e4\u05bc\u05b0\u05e0\u05b5\u05d9 (peney) is a Hebrew noun derived from the root \u05e4\u05b8\u05e0\u05b8\u05d4 (pana), meaning 'to turn' or 'face'. In biblical context, it primarily signifies 'faces', but also symbolizes presence, direction, and attention. Theologically, faces represent individuals' relationship with God (Psalm 24:6). Historically, face-to-face encounters signified covenantal intimacy (Exodus 33:11), while turning away denoted rebellion (Isaiah 59:2). In the New Testament, Christ's 'face' embodies divine revelation and salvation (Matthew 24:30)."
